parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent ABS/VSA Warning Light and Brake System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the ABS/VSA system and brake system can cause loss of braking power, leading to accidents and potential fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS/VSA warning light comes on intermittently
the brake pedal is difficult to depress
the brake pedal is extremely stiff
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle has no power assist braking
the vehicle is unable to stop.
